11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Hankyns was born about 1500, in Dymock, Gloucestershire, England, his father, William Daniel Hankins, was 51 and his mother, Margaret Lettice, was 37. He married Anne Hungerford about 1524, in Dymock, Gloucestershire, England. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. His occupation is listed as vicar hankyns in Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom. He died on 21 March 1538, in Forest of Dean, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 39, and was buried in Dymock, Gloucestershire, England, United Kingdom."},"et":{"abt 1500–21 March 1538":"umbes 1500–21. märts 1538","1500–1538":"1500–1538","1511–1611":"1511–1611","1525–1569":"1525–1569","1540–Male":"1540–Surnud","1535–1569":"1535–1569","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1465–1500":"1465–1500","1450":"1450","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","abt 1500":"umbes 1500","1535":"1535","1512":"1512","1611":"1611","1500":"1500","21 March 1538":"21. märts 1538","1511":"1511","1465":"1465","about 1524":"umbes 1524","1540":"1540","1538":"1538","Dymock,Gloucestershire, England":"Dymock, Gloucestershire, England","Dymock, Gloucestershire, England":"Dymock, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dymock, Forest of Dean District,  Gloucestershire, England":"Forest of Dean, Gloucestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"abt 1500–21 March 1538":"noin 1500–21. maaliskuuta 1538","1500–1538":"1500–1538","1511–1611":"1511–1611","1525–1569":"1525–1569","1540–Male":"1540–Kuollut","1535–1569":"1535–1569","1450–1512":"1450–1512","1465–1500":"1465–1500","1450":"1450","1525":"1525","1569":"1569","abt 1500":"noin 1500","1535":"1535","1512":"1512","1611":"1611","1500":"1500","21 March 1538":"21. maaliskuuta 1538","1511":"1511",